    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and slice finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-tail-on-jumbo-prawns/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Zest your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Cut the <strong>zested</strong> <strong>lemon[s] </strong>into 4 wedges per lemon</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-tail-on-jumbo-prawns/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>in 450ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[675ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [900ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> and stir in your <strong>soft cheese </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-tail-on-jumbo-prawns/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>lemon zest </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-tail-on-jumbo-prawns/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>orzo </strong>to the pan with the juice of 1/4 of the <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>stock </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy leek orzo</strong></p><p>Tip: Stir the orzo occasionally to stop it from sticking!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-tail-on-jumbo-prawns/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat, once hot, drain, then add your <strong>tail on jumbo prawns</strong> and cook for 4-5 min</p><p>Tear in your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and the juice of 1/4 of the <strong>lemon wedges </strong>and cook for 2-3 min further or until the prawns are cooked through and the<strong> </strong>'Nduja has broken down \u2013 these are your <strong>'Nduja tail on jumbo prawns</strong></p><p>Tip: Keep the heat medium to avoid the 'Nduja from smoking!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-tail-on-jumbo-prawns/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the orzo is cooked through, season generously with <strong>black pepper</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon wedges </strong>to a bowl with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> lemony dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-leek-orzo-with-nduja-tail-on-jumbo-prawns/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy leek orzo</strong> with the <strong>'Nduja tail on jumbo prawns</strong> over the top - this is your<strong> creamy leek orzo with 'Nduja tail on jumbo prawns</strong></p><p>Spoon any<strong> remaining 'Nduja oil </strong>from the pan over the orzo</p><p>Serve the<strong> salad</strong> to the side drizzled with the <strong>lemony dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
